				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Nerfs that would make sense<a name="56282"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 11 04 11:32 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, I've been reading these boards a lot lately, and have seen a great deal being said in favor of improving the power of bards.  However, as we all know, the Dev giveth and the Dev taketh away, so with our improvements, will likely come a nerf.  So...why not have BARDS decide what should get nerfed?  Here's what I'd suggest to start with.
<br />

<br />
1.  Practice, practice, practice.  Being a musician in real life, I know the value of practice.  If you don't practice music, you get WORSE at it!  What I would suggest, is that, without constant practice in various instruments, we will actually LOSE skill (or recieve a temporary negative modifier).
<br />
Effect on the average player: They can't just be an afk Marr bot, and expect to be able to pacify with maxed woodwind skill because they were afk practicing 3 months ago.  I know if I tried to play a flute after 2 years (that's 36 days of EQ time), I would suck miserably.  This may encourage bards to diversify more, and actually USE some of those obscure songs.
<br />

<br />
2.  A 25% penalty on a  P/S instrument while wielding a weapon in secondary.  I know I play guitar a LOT better using two hands  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />.  
<br />

<br />
3.  Consider lowering Psalm of Veeshan effects in PVP.  I don't play on a PVP server, but from what I hear, Bards are to PVP what Amazons are to Diablo2 (cheap and overpowered).  Any PVP server bards able to confirm or deny?
<br />

<br />

<br />
I submit these suggestions, not because I hate bards, but because I love them, and would rather see us get nerfed in ways that don't totally ruin our effectiveness.  Anyone else have ideas on this subject?  Flames?  Bueller?</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.pravda-of-norrath.com/">Midwinter</a> 
