				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Nerfs that would make sense<a name="56305"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 12 04 1:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>1) well then by that logic i would want melees to loose skill in their weapon skill..chances are a warriors 2hb doesnt get used much when he gets hit BoC and such...casters should loose some of their abjuration every once in a while.  In any event, i think the only instrument that would have a chance of going downis winds, even then i doubt it.  I tend to use every instrument type daily.
<br />

<br />
2) The mod on an instrument is due to its magical nature..does tha magic stop working?  What about our epic? i dont see any strings, a mouthpiece, and i doubt its hollow enough to drum with.
<br />

<br />

<br />
3) could care less, most people dont play on PvP.  EQ's PvP systems sucks, i don't understand why anyone plays it.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I think you are misunderstanding the reason people want these modifications.  The simple fact is, bards are being trivialized in certain areas.  Our melee damage output is horrid, our damage mitigation is almost non-existant, i've seen casters tank better than most bards.  Even when we can tank..we cant.  We cant hold aggro, one heal and its gone.  Our ability to boost the groups efficiency are being edged out by some the new insane gear and AA's.  Sure we can grind out lots of AA solo, IF the areas that dont have summoning mobs arent taken, but it's usually faster with a group anyway.  
<br />

<br />
Sony has done a horrible job with keeping the class defining lines from being blurred.  With each expansion, the classes are becoming more alike. Bards being the jack of all trades,  get left out.  We're tired of being left out.  We want to be brought up to the rest of EQ.  Personally i would like to see the rest of eq brought down. The numbers have gotten out of hand.  There should be no reason why items/stats/skills that exist in the old world should be considered utter trash by todays standards. </span></td>
