				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Nerfs that would make sense<a name="56359"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 12 04 9:47 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Getting numbers under control does not mean we have to loose playability.  However, there does need to be a design paradigm that can keep some of this mess in check.  There could be a happy medium where things were not as weak as they were in old world, but no where near as strong as current standards.  Velious content comes to mind.  Its still good without being overly powerful.  But some of this new GoD stuff..a bracer that has more ac and stats than breastplates that were considered uber not long ago...it doesnt take a genious to follow the pattern.
<br />

<br />
tanking: your confusing should and could.  Given a better alternative the bard should not tank, however we ARE a plate class.  We should be able to tank if the situation arises, but our lack of damage mitigation and ability to hold aggro seriously hamper that.  As i said before, there are silk wears that can tank better than we can.  Silk vs plate..this physics just doesnt add up.
<br />

<br />
Bards becoming little more than a mana battery? We're barely that now.  With all the new spells and the huge amount of mana regen items, we're slowly becoming less needed.  Sure people wont mind having another 20 mana regen, but when they start regenning 100+ points a tick, and can be at full mana in  just a couple minutes anyway it becomes far less important.</span></td>
