				<td colspan="2"><span>The basic thesis seems to be that Nerfing is inevitable, so perhaps we should pick out some nice Nerfs for ourselves.  The premise does not work for me.  Any hits with the Nerf Bat of Doom will happen no matter what we might suggest.
<br />

<br />
As for the ideas...
<br />

<br />
Skill decay:  What would that do in the game exactly?  Increase downtime is all.  Instead of being out playing the game, you would have to sit and train.  Would it encourage the use of alternate songs?  No.  You use the right tool for the right job.  Trying to use second best is just going to make you ineffective.
<br />

<br />
I must also note that this would not do a *thing* to Nerf the class.  It would just create a nuisance.  I submit that adding things to make the game less fun is a bad idea.
<br />

<br />
Lowering our effectiveness when holding a weapon and an instrument:  What would this do in game?  Make the benefit of Primary Hand instruments irrelevant.  It would also drive the price up on items that have an instrument mod, since it would make actually using an instrument even *less* attractive than it already is.
<br />

<br />
I can't speak to PvP changes.  I have no interest in PvP.</span></td>
