				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Nerfs that would make sense<a name="57073"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 17 04 9:15 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Or you could actually just... you know... live.
<br />

<br />
My take on things is sketchy at best, to be honest.  It seems to me like making characters higher maintenance would be pretty detrimental to most people's enjoyment of the game.  Even if you see it as more realistic, or interesting, I see it as a Pain in the a$ that I wouldn't want to deal with.  But really, I think it could be funny.  So here I go!
<br />

<br />
You want realistic?  Here's EQ gone real...  Give everyone a gun cause swords just suck.  Mobs don't respawn; once you kill em, they're dead for good.  Bards?  Don't get me started on them.  The last time I tried Chords of Dissonance on my guitar, the guy in the room next to mine just got pissed off and told me to turn my amplifier down.  So bards are useless now.  No more magic, no more rezzing the dead, etc etc.  So really the only thing you can do is go around killing things with your gun.  Since mobs in the real world don't respawn, there's not gonna be many of them left at the rate that they're hunted.  So you're not going to have any good targets.  No targets, no money.  Well, at least there's tradeskills to make money from, right?  Let's choose brewing, that's a good one.  Except you're nobody but some poor hunter with no targets, so you've got no market appeal on your beverages.  So what do you do? Get drunk.  Since you have no money, you'll be living with your parents.  So you'll stumble in at 4am, after brewing for hours, selling nothing in the bazaar, then drinking yourself stupid, while your parents are sitting there waiting for you, screaming &quot;Why couldn't you have gone to Erudin and studied!?  Look at yourself!  You could have been a researcher for crying out loud!&quot;  Then you'll pass out and wake up at about 2pm in a liquid you don't want to identify.  Of course, you'll have some horrible hangover so all your skills will be impaired for when you go hunting next weekend for targets that probably won't be there.  You'll probably shoot off a finger (or at least put a hole in your foot) when you mistake a friend sneaking around in the dark of blackburrow for a gnoll and try to score it big.  Then you'll somehow stagger back home and call for a healer.  But since magic has gone bye bye, and magic is all that clerics know, you'll probably call for someone who knows how to bandage instead.  Who better to bind wound than a monk or warrior?  Then one day, your life seriously changes.  A big hunter's guild invites you to a raid.  Raid style is a little different now.  Just think of an advancing army or something.  Anyway, they decide they're gonna go after a god.  They're not happy with their diety anymore, and they need all the manpower they can get.  So you strap on your kevlar helmet, grab your trusty shotgun, and head out with your buddies.  Now magic may be dead, but gods are still gods.  They're going to be omnipotent.  So your advancing army is going to start firing, and Mithaniel Marr is just gonna look at you and say &quot;Aw crap, here we go again.  Stupid people.&quot;  Then you would all die in a huge fiery blast.  Is this the kind of game you want?  Cause it's actually starting to sound like fun now that I think about it.
<br />

<br />
Sorry I kinda hijacked the main topic.  I just wanted to have fun <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /></span></td>
